# Global gitignore — stowed to ~/.gitignore_global, wired up via core.excludesFile
# in .gitconfig (same package).
#
# Scope: junk produced by the *machine* or the *editor*, which no repo of mine should
# ever have to care about. Project-level artifacts (build output, deps, caches) belong
# in that project's own .gitignore, not here — a global rule that hides a real file is
# far harder to debug than a missing one.

